Variables
Use ESV variables to set configuration values that need to be different for each tenant environment.
Variables are simple key-value pairs. Unlike secrets, they are not versioned. They should not contain sensitive values. The value of
a variable must not exceed a maximum length of 65535 bytes (just under 64KiB).
You can reference ESV variables from configuration placeholders or scripts after you:
Create or update the variables using the variables APIs or the Advanced Identity Cloud admin console.
Restart Advanced Identity Cloud services using the restart API or by applying updates in the Advanced Identity Cloud
admin console.
