Secret versions
Instead of having a single value, ESV secrets have one or more secret versions, each containing their own value. By design, the
value of a secret version cannot be read back after it has been created. The value of a secret version must not exceed a maximum
length of 65535 bytes (just under 64KiB).
To create a new secret version, its value must be different from the value of the latest secret version. If you try to create a new
secret version with the same value as the latest version, the existing version is retained and no changes are made.
You can enable or disable secret versions by setting their status field to ENABLED or DISABLED using the REST API or clicking the
Active toggle in the admin console. The latest version of a secret must be enabled for it to be used in your configuration.
The following rules ensure that a secret always has at least one enabled version:
When you create a secret, the first version of the secret is automatically created and is enabled.
You cannot disable the latest version of a secret.
You cannot delete the latest version of a secret if the previous version is disabled.
