PingOne Advanced Identity Cloud lets you store signing and encryption keys in ESV secrets, then map them to secret labels. Each
secret label represents an authentication feature in Advanced Identity Cloud, such as signing OAuth 2.0 client access tokens.
Advanced Identity Cloud can directly access keys stored in a mapped ESV secret, there is no need to restart Advanced Identity
