When you update a secret, the new secret value is used immediately.
When rotating SAML 2.0 certificates, as soon as you update the secret with the new certificate value, the new
certificate is used for signing or encryption. This means you need to coordinate updating the secret with the
remote entity provider. If the remote entity provider hasn’t imported the updated metadata, federation will fail
because you are using different certificates.
