Configure placeholders to use with ESVs.
PingOne Advanced Identity Cloud lets you reference ESVs from configuration placeholders. This lets you use different
configuration values for the development, staging, and production environments at runtime.
For example, suppose you wanted to set a different email sender for each environment. You would set the configuration value of
the email sender to an ESV with different values in each environment; for example, dev-mycompany@example.com (development),
staging-mycompany@example.com (staging), and mycompany@example.com (production). Then, you would insert the ESV
configuration placeholder into your configuration instead of a literal value.
