Who owns the configuration in my environments?
You own and are responsible for the configuration in your tenant environments. Although Ping Identity manages and supports
the Advanced Identity Cloud platform, you are accountable for creating, applying, updating, and supporting the configuration
applied to the platform to meet your specific use cases.
Can I partially promote configuration? Or promote the configuration for an individual realm?
Ping Identity promotes static configuration for the whole environment, so promotions always include all realms and all other
static configuration. It is therefore not possible to promote partial configuration of any kind between environments, or promote
the configuration for an individual realm between environments.
What kind of configuration changes can my company make?
Ping Identity considers configuration to be either dynamic or static.
