Show details
The journey gathers behavioral data from the user’s session
and determines a risk level. Depending on the assessed risk,
the journey takes different paths:
Low risk : The journey proceeds, but also checks for
indicators such as a new device or other suspicious
parameters.
Medium to high risk : Increases the required
authentication level, asking for stronger user
verification before continuing.
Specific threats (for example, bots or man-in-the-
middle): Checks if the user’s account is active. If it is,
the account is disabled, and an alert email is sent to
the user.
Failure : If any part of the risk evaluation fails, the
journey logs the failure and terminates.
