Show details
The journey starts by identifying an existing user. It then
proceeds as follows:
Initial assessment : Calculates a KBA threshold based
on factors such as the user’s transaction history and
timestamps. This determines if they need to answer
security questions.
Authorization policy : The initial assessment is sent to
a PingOne Authorize policy. The policy decides
whether to:
Permit the request, allowing the user to
proceed.
Challenge the user with security questions.
Challenge : If challenged, the user is presented with a
security question. Their response is sent back to the
PingOne Authorize policy for a new decision.
This cycle repeats until the user is permitted or
denied. A denial also occurs if the user runs out of
questions.
The specific questions used for the challenge are configured
in the PingOne Authorize policy’s statements. Learn more in
