With the Advanced Identity Cloud authentication with threat detection journey, the user’s geographical location is evaluated as
part of a real-time threat detection process. If a user attempts to sign on from a location that exceeds a defined radius from the
user’s expected location, it’s considered medium or high risk, depending on the extent of the deviation. The user is either
prompted to step up with multi-factor authentication (MFA) or is denied access. If authentication is blocked or requires further
verification, the user is notified by email or SMS to confirm that the attempt was legitimate.
