You can provide Advanced Identity Cloud with additional information about how a user is authenticating. For example, you can
specify a particular authentication journey, or request a list of the authentication services that would satisfy an authentication
condition.
The following example specifies the Login journey by using the authIndexType and authIndexValue parameters:
$ --request POST \curl \
