The /json/authenticate endpoint supports callback mechanisms to perform complex authentication journeys. When Advanced
Identity Cloud needs to return or request information, it returns a JSON object with the authentication step, the authentication
identifier, and the related callbacks.
The following callback types are available:
Read-only callbacks
Read-only callbacks provide information to the user, such as text messages or the period of time a user must wait before
continuing their authentication journey.
