"tokenId":"AQIC5wM...TU3OQ*", "successUrl": "/enduser/?realm=/alpha",
"realm":"/alpha"}
The returned tokenID is called a session token (also referred to as an SSO token). Each REST API call made after successful
authentication must present the session token in the HTTP header as proof of authentication.
Call one or more additional REST APIs on behalf of the authenticated user.
