For example:
"output": [ {
"name": "prompt", "value": " User Name: "
} ],
"input": [ {
"name": "IDToken1", "value": ""
}]
The value of some interactive callbacks can be returned as headers, such as the X-OpenAM-Username and X-OpenAM-Password
headers, but most of them must be returned in JSON as a response to the request.
Depending on how complex the authentication journey is, Advanced Identity Cloud could return several callbacks sequentially.
Each must be completed and returned to Advanced Identity Cloud until authentication is successful.
