emergency_home^ Social authentication nodes expect every attribute to have a value. In other words, the attributes returned by
the identity provider can’t be empty or null, or the journey will end with an error.
For example, if a user tries to log in using Google as the identity provider, but they didn’t configure a surname
in their account, Google returns null as the value of the familyName for the identity, and social
authentication fails.
Ensure all users have their social profiles configured correctly, or modify the transformation scripts so that they
don’t collect null or empty attributes.
